# OpenTimestamps Bitcoin Anchor - INSTRUCTIONS

This file provides instructions for creating the Bitcoin timestamp (.ots file) for SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md

## CRITICAL: Network Access Required

The OpenTimestamps calendar servers are not accessible from the GitHub Actions environment due to network restrictions. This timestamp MUST be created from a system with full internet access.

## Method 1: Using PowerShell (Windows/PowerShell Core)

```powershell
# This is the working command from the problem statement
iwr https://btc.calendar.catallaxy.com -Method POST -Body ([System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes((Get-Content .\SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md -Raw))) -ContentType "application/octet-stream" -OutFile SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots
```

## Method 2: Using OpenTimestamps CLI (Linux/macOS/Windows)

```bash
# Install OpenTimestamps client
pip install opentimestamps-client

# Create timestamp
ots stamp SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md

# This creates SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots
```

## Method 3: Using curl (Linux/macOS)

```bash
curl -X POST https://btc.calendar.catallaxy.com \
  -H "Content-Type: application/octet-stream" \
  --data-binary @SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md \
  -o SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots
```

## Method 4: Using ots.btc.catallaxy.com

```bash
curl -X POST https://ots.btc.catallaxy.com/timestamp \
  -H "Content-Type: application/octet-stream" \
  --data-binary @SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md \
  -o SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots
```

## Verification After Creation

Once the .ots file is created, verify it:

```bash
# Using OpenTimestamps CLI
ots verify SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots

# Or using info command
ots info SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md.ots
```

## What the .ots File Contains

The .ots file is a cryptographic proof that:
1. The SHA256 hash of SOVEREIGN_MANIFEST_v1.0.md was submitted to the Bitcoin blockchain
2. It was included in a specific Bitcoin block at a specific time
3. This proof is independently verifiable forever

